1787, Giles Hooker died in Farmington at age 96. When the news reached his older brother Samuel — then age 98 in Kensington — Samuel \"fell back in his chair and expired\" on March 1, 1787. Two brothers, together accounting for nearly 195 years of life, died within ten days of each other."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"The well stone on Main Street","body":"He and Martha lived on the George Cowles place on Main Street, Farmington. In Edward Hooker's time (1909), a flat stone in the sidewalk just below the brow of the hill still covered the old well of the Giles Hooker house. Directly opposite, his father Rev. Samuel Hooker had lived in the Mix House — just south of the old burying ground."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Lt. Giles Hooker","title":"Lieutenant","first_name":"Giles","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"giles-hooker-1690"},"I00121":{"id":"I00121","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1693,"month":6,"day":2,"city":"Hartford","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1760,"month":5,"day":22,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X00110","mother_id":"X00111"},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00087","date_year":1720,"location_city":"Farmington","location_county":"Hartford","location_state":"Connecticut","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1760,"children_ids":["H00232"]}],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 87"}],"gender":"female","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_no